1991-04-16  dickey@software.org

	* src/version.h: absorb backslash in shell command only when "#" or "%"
	follows (briefer).

	* src/ded.c: suppress empty-strings from argument list

	* src/deddoit.c:
	absorb backslash only when it precedes "#" or "%", to make
	typing commands with backslashes simpler (though inconsistent).
	also, made the static buffers auto (cleaner code).

	* src/version.h:
	modified so that "-" argument causes DED to read a list of
	arguments from stdin (no wildcard expansion!)

	* src/ded.c: interpret "-" argument as read-from-standard-input

